Dane wejsciowe to wyniki ankiety przeprowadzonej na grupie mieszkańców USA.
Ankietowani odpowiedzieli na pytania:
-In general, how worried are you about earthquakes? (Not at all worried-Extremely worried)
-How worried are you about the Big One, a massive, catastrophic earthquake? (Not at all worried-Extremely worried)
-Do you think the "Big One" will occur in your lifetime? (No/Yes)
-Have you ever experienced an earthquake? (No/Yes, one or more minor ones/Yes, one or more major ones)
-Have you or anyone in your household taken any precautions for an earthquake (packed an earthquake survival kit, prepared an evacuation plan, etc.)? (No/Yes)
-How familiar are you with the San Andreas Fault line? (Not at all familiar-Extremely familiar)
-How familiar are you with the Yellowstone Supervolcano? (Not at all familiar-Extremely familiar)

Odpowiedzieli też na pytania dotyczące ich danych osobowych:
- Age (Years)
- What is your gender? (Female/Male)
- How much total combined money did all members of your HOUSEHOLD earn last year? ($)
- US Region (Geographical Region) 